  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the trial is the analysis of safety and efficacy of the chymase inhibitor
      BAY1142524 at a dose of 25 mg BID in comparison to placebo using a 6 months treatment period
      in patients with left-ventricular (LV) dysfunction after myocardial infarction (MI).
      BAY1142524 or placebo will be given on top of evidence-based standard of care for
      left-ventricular dysfunction after myocardial infarction. Primary objective is the analysis
      of first signs of efficacy as determined by favourable changes in functional parameters of
      adverse cardiac remodelling (i.e. endsystolic and enddiastolic volume index, ejection
      fraction). Secondary objective is the analysis of safety and tolerability as evidenced by the
      incidence and severity of adverse events. 30 patients have to complete treatment with verum
      and 30 patients have to complete treatment with placebo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
